In this article, President Biden expresses his motivation to take action on gun reform. He mentions meeting with victims of gun violence and their families, highlighting the palpable pain they experience. When asked about sending long-range rocket systems to Ukraine, he clarifies that the US will not send any systems that can strike into Russia. On the question of how Republicans will approach gun reform now, the President states that he hasn't spoken to them, but believes they will have to take a hard look at the issue. He also discusses the need for rational gun laws and the irrationality of high-caliber weapons. President Biden acknowledges the limitations of his power as President and expresses the importance of persuasion and executive actions. He mentions that there seems to be a realization among rational Republicans, including Senator McConnell and Senator Cornyn, that the current situation regarding gun violence cannot continue.